               <msContents>
                  <summary>The property of Petesouchos is divided between his son, Petesouchos and his daughter Tapeteus. The property consists of 1. unidentified holdings near Kerkesoucha (l. 5); 2. one aroura of a catoechic allotment (ll. 5-23); an uncertain amount of sacred land (ll. 6-23); 4. a share of a date-palm garden (line 7); 5. some shares of house property otherwise undescribed (lines 8-24); and 6. the usual household goods, etc. (ll. 9-10).</summary>
